goals.question: What is the trend of deaths caused by disasters over time?

goals.question: What is the distribution of deaths caused by disasters for each entity?
goals.visualization: box plot of Deaths over Entity

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of deaths caused by disasters over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['Deaths'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Deaths'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by disasters?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.title('Which entity has the highest number of deaths caused by disasters?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('Entity').sum().reset_index()
    plt.scatter(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the entity and the number of deaths caused by disasters?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Entity')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Entity'] == entity]['Deaths'] for entity in data['Entity'].unique()])
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['Entity'].unique(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by disasters for each entity?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
